Ticket Information for Friday’s game against Whiteface

Tickets will go on sale to our Parents of our high school student athletes, Monday August 31st. Tickets will be available at 12pm and will be $4 (Parents) and $2 (Student tickets). Families will be limited to only 3 tickets per household.

Tickets to the general public will go on sale Tuesday, September 1st through the week leading to the game. General Public $4 and Student $2.

Tickets are limited and are on a first come first serve basis! Information regarding tickets will be updated on our facebook page to the quantity left to the general public.

REGISTRATION INFORMATION:

Registration will be held on Monday the 17th and Tuesday the 18th at 10-11:30 and 2-4. Monday will be for last names ending in A-L and Tuesday last names ending in M-Z. This will be a drive thru registration. Please follow the following steps:

1. Pick up packets
2. Park to fill out paper work
3. Drive up to packet drop off

New students to the district will need to bring the following:

1. Birth certificate
2. Social security card
3. Shot records
4. Parent’s driver license
5. Proof of residency

Please contact Tiffany at tgarza@wilsonisd.org if any of these times do not work for you to make other arrangements.

Officer escort on US HWY 87 Wednesday:
Lynn County Sheriff’s Office is coordinating an escort of the body of Sheriff Abraham Vega from Dallas to Lubbock on Wednesday, July 15, which will be joined by other local and area law enforcement and first responders.

Wilson citizens who want to show their respect may be stationed on the side of the road Wednesday on US HWY 87 and FM 211 as the escort passes through Wilson at approximately 3:15 p.m. on its way to Resthaven Funeral Home in Lubbock. Please line up starting around 3:00p.m. If standing outside vehicles, officers ask that citizens please wear masks and social distance from others.

Today’s workout

This will be a three round phase. You complete one station and move on to the next and so on. Once you get back to the top of list, that completes one round. You will have to repeat for three rounds.

Example: 1. Wide (5x5), Burpee(5x5), military push ups (5x5), jumping jacks (5x10). Congrats you finished one round! Then repeat two more times!! Hold yourself accountable when completing workouts.

Parents and student athletes of Wilson ISD,

We will put student safety and health first. This has been a difficult decision, but we have postponed our summer strength and conditioning program back a week, beginning June 22, 2020. We will continue to monitor cases of COVID-19 in our county. Workouts will be posted through our social media account to do at home. Thank you for your patience and understanding.
text:

We will continue to monitor cases of COVID-19 in our county. Workouts will be posted through our social media account to do at home. Thank you for your patience and understanding.

post_text: With the recent spikes of COVID-19 in our neighboring towns, we will be closely monitoring the current situations. Our first priority is the safety of our student athletes. post_text:
Due to COVID 19, graduation will be looking a little different this year. Wilson ISD has decided to have a drive thru graduation in front of central office on Saturday, May 23rd at 10AM pending TEA approval.

In order to practice social distancing, each graduate will be allowed to have three vehicles. One vehicle for the graduate and two others for their guest. These vehicles will be given passes to place on their windshield. The graduate will be the only person allowed to get out their vehicles to receive their diplomas. Everyone else must remain in the vehicle. Wilson ISD has hired a professional photographer to capture this moment. Each graduate will receive one photo and flash drive with all the pictures taken.

post_text:
Seniors,
The governors decision today has made it difficult for your teachers and I to believe that our last moment with you was THE last moment for the year.
The faculty and staff at Wilson ISD misses our kiddos in the halls and in the classrooms. Graduation plans are being discussed and we do have some creative ideas in mind. We will celebrate your hard work and achievements because we know the importance of this milestone in your life, please do not despair. This is an unusual moment in all of our lives but as Wilson Mustangs we will show our strength and perseverance. Please feel free to reach out to us for support. We are here for you and no virus can stop that. Please be safe.

Thank you,

Mr. Portillo

All updates will be provided through our website and Facebook page.

post_text:
Today Wilson ISD was one of 25 school districts to receive a check for the high demand job training grant. These grants are made possible from the Lubbock Economic Development Alliance, South Plains Workforce Solutions, and the Texas Workforce Commission. Wilson ISD received the largest amount totaling $128,728.65. This grant has allowed our district to initiate our STEM, HVAC and Welding Programs.

We would like to say a HUGE thank you to Coach Garza for putting in the work to allow our district to receive this grant. We are grateful to have someone like you to make these things possible for our students.
